    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Game played on a rectangular field with a nettled goal at each end, in which two teams of eleven players each compete to drive a small leather ball into each other's goal using a stick with a curved end.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046684/Random House Unabridged Dictionary (1993)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>在長方形場地上進行的比賽，場地兩端各有一個網狀球門，由兩隊各11名隊員參賽，各自運用末端彎曲的長棍子將小皮球帶入對方球門中。
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Spiel auf einem rechteckigen Feld mit einem Netztor an jedem Ende, bei dem zwei Mannschaften mit je elf Spielern gegeneinander antreten, indem sie versuchen, einen kleinen Lederball mit einem Stock mit gebogenem Ende in das gegnerische Tor zu schlagen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
